  <bioghist id="aspace_facbb052459770c14362001c16c2d617">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Francis H. Scheetz, a prominent Philadelphia lawyer, was a member of the Cornell University Board of Trustees from 1951-1967, and then a trustee emeritus and presidential councillor until his death in 1968. He was a recipient of the Cornell Medal for outstanding service to the University. (Cornell University Class of 1916)</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_55934f60a12aff1eedb2bea441e73772">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Includes materials relating to Scheetz' student days, including lecture notes, diplomas, and Cornell Class of 1916 correspondence and reunion and fundraising material; papers from his work as a Cornell trustee and presidential councillor concerning student housing, Cornell United Religious Work, information concerning the Faculty Committee on Academic Freedom and Tenure, the Charles J. Quillman, Jr. Fellowship (1952-1964), Cornell Club of New York, Marquis Foundation, Society for the Humanities, Glee Club, the Cornell Laboratory of Ornithology, the Aeronautical Laboratory, Cornell University Survey of Administrative Management (Volumes 1-5), student affairs, and minutes and other materials of the University Council and Trustees. Also, photographs; prints; four world maps prepared for King Louis XV of France (1740, 1741); a portrait of General Henry Dearborn, a Revolutionary War patriot; two Sèvres vases (gifts to General Dearborn from Louis Philippe); information concerning the Xth International Congress on the History of Science (1962); Theta Delta Chi correspondence; postcards; Scheetz' biographical data; and World War I officer training information.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_1237417d480362fd15fb94ed9a391ab5">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>Francis Harley Scheetz Papers, #2-10-1109. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
